What is Monitoring?
Monitoring = checking if your system is OK or NOT
It answers questions like:
❓ Is my server up or down?
❓ Is CPU or memory too high?
❓ Is my app responding slowly?
❓ Did something break?
In Prometheus terms:
Prometheus collects metrics like:
CPU usage
Memory usage
Disk space
HTTP request count
Error rate
👉 Example:
CPU usage > 80% for 5 minutes → ALERT 🚨
Simple definition:
Monitoring tells you WHEN something is wrong

🧠 What is Observability?
Observability = understanding WHY something is wrong
It goes deeper than monitoring.
It answers:
❓ Why is my app slow?
❓ Which service is causing the issue?
❓ Is it DB, network, or code?
❓ Which API is failing and for which user?
Observability is based on 3 pillars:
Metrics – numbers (Prometheus)
Logs – detailed text (ELK / Loki)
Traces – request flow (Jaeger / Tempo)
Simple definition:
Observability tells you WHY and WHERE the problem happened

🛠️ Role of Prometheus & Grafana
🟢 Prometheus (Monitoring + part of Observability)
Collects metrics from apps, nodes, Kubernetes
Stores time-series data
Evaluates alert rules
Example metrics:
http_requests_total
node_cpu_seconds_total
container_memory_usage_bytes
👉 Prometheus is mainly Monitoring, but also contributes to Observability (metrics part)

📊 Grafana (Visualization & Observability UI)
Shows data as dashboards
Connects to:
Prometheus (metrics)
Loki (logs)
Tempo / Jaeger (traces)
Grafana helps you:
Visualize trends
Correlate metrics + logs + traces
Debug issues faster
👉 Grafana = Observability dashboard

