🧩 Real-world Example (Very Important)
Scenario:
Users say “App is slow”
Monitoring (Prometheus):
CPU: ✅ OK
Memory: ✅ OK
App is UP: ✅
➡️ Monitoring says: “Everything looks fine 🤷”
Observability (Grafana + Logs + Traces):
Slow API endpoint identified
DB query taking 5 seconds
Only happening for one service
➡️ Observability says:
“The /login API is slow because DB query is slow”

🧠 One-line summary (Interview Gold ✨)
Monitoring tells you that a problem exists.
Observability tells you why the problem exists.
